Oscar 'Papoo' Hernandez Jr has pleaded guilty to weapons charges in connection to the death of Odin Lloyd, the semi-professional football player in 2013 .
Hernandez was sentenced to life in prison without the possibility of parole for first-degree murder in the 2013 shooting death of semi-pro football player Odin Lloyd .
He is now facing up to 30 months in prison after pleading guilty to charges of transporting firearms across state lines, obstruction of justice and witness tampering .